race.comment: TERILEE (3) resumes. She showed plenty of ability in four runs last time in, winning dominantly here on debut before measuring up in some good 3yo races. Takes on the older horses and gives away fitness but fancy she could end up being better than this grade. MERCURIAL LADY (5) is a consistent mare who got the job done at $1.75 last start at Sale in this grade. She's drawn wide but rolls forward and can take catching. TOURNELLE (7) is fresh for this but racing in fine form of late. The win two back rated well, a repeat of that goes close. Wary of WINGS OF DESIRE (8) who is now with Grahame Begg, formerly with Michael Freedman. A relation to Winx, her best form would go close in this but 1200m from a wide draw might be on the sharp side.
